data.description:
Significant Price Reduction! Welcome to the waterfront community of Oak Harbour. This marina community is nestled on the Intracoastal waterway with beautiful Oak Tree lined streets where homes rarely become available. This home has been meticulously maintained by the same family for 33 years.  When you enter the home you will immediately notice the high vaulted ceiling in the main living area offering multiple windows with custom draperies and wonderful natural light.   The large eat in kitchen has an oversized center island that has recently been updated with new counter tops.  There is no shortage of storage in this kitchen with slide-out drawers in virtually every storage space and a built in pantry.  The kitchen opens to a comfortable family room which allows for easy entertaining. The first floor also has a large formal dining room, living area with wood burning fireplace, and powder room.  The large rear screened in patio has wonderful privacy from mature landscaping, and allows you to access the patio from the formal living room or family room.   The second floor has a very functional split floor plan with the large master bedroom on one side.  The master bath offers a recently renovated glass enclosed shower with custom tile and a separate large soaking tub.  The master bath also has a large double sink vanity and ample storage. On the other side of the second floor you will find 2 large guest bedrooms, a second full bath, and large loft area with closet which could be your 4th bedroom, office, or additional family space.  
This community offers you the ability to be in a private, secure, waterfront community, with its own marina and private boat slips.  There are currently private boat slips available for rent and owners in the community get first right of refusal when one comes for sale.  Oak Harbor has 2 community pools, tennis courts, fitness center, and a great club house where neighbors regularly gather.  Located minutes from fine dining and shopping on PGA Blvd, Downtown at the Gardens, other local marinas, less than 5 minutes from some of the most beautiful beaches in Florida, easy access to interstate 95, Florida's turnpike, and only 20 minutes to Palm Beach International Airport.
